data.text:
Profession: Princess of Orange

Biography: Daughter of Charles I, Landgrave of Hesse-Kassel, and Maria Amalia of Courland.

By her marriage to Johan Willem Friso, Prince of Orange, she became Princess consort of Orange, a title last held by Mary II of England.

Like her husband, she is an ancestor of all currently reigning monarchs in Europe.

Born: February 7, 1688

Birthplace: Kassel, Hesse-Kassel

Star Sign: Aquarius

Died: April 9, 1765 (aged 77)

Personal Life

Frisian Stadtholder and Prince of Orange John William Friso (21) weds Dutch Countess Maria Louise van Hessen-Kassel (21), until his death in 1702
